was living in 1324 and 1365.\n\nJohn was the son and heir of Roger Domville, Lord of Brimstage and Oxton, living in 1313. Roger, John's father, was the son and heir of Sir Roger Domville, Lord of Brimstage and Oxton, died 1289, and his first wife, Margaret Venables, daughter of Roger Venables of Kinderton. Brimstage and Oxton were in Wirral hundred, Cheshire, England.\n\n«b»John married twice:«/b»\nMatilda, daughter of Sir William Brereton of Brereton; John and his first wife had children:\n\n1.) John Domville, Lord of Brimstage and Oxton, born circa 1310, died 1394, married Cecilia, daughter of William de Mobberley, she was living in 1404;\n\n2.) Robert Domville, was living in 1333 and 1342, married Agnes, daughter of Thomas de Legh, and they were the progenitors of the Domvilles of Iamine;\n\n3.) Thomas Domville, was living in 1342, married Margaret, daughter of Thomas de Legh;\n\n4.) Matthew Domville, was living in 1357, died o.s.p.s [died without having children], married Agnes, daughter of William de Wettenhall, Agnes died in 1418;\n\nMatilda, widow of William de Mobberley; John and his second wife had no children.\n\nJohn Domville died after 1365.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1280","date":"about 1280","place":"Oxton, Cheshire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1289","date":"1289","place":"Cheshire, England","age":"9","id":"LHGV-BFG"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1310","date":"1310","age":"30","id":"GM18-BVP"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1315","date":"1315","place":"Oxton, Woodchurch, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","age":"35","id":"KG3W-537"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1322","date":"1322","place":"Oxton Brunstath, Cheshire, England","age":"42","id":"G6HH-Q8K"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1322","date":"1322","place":"England","age":"42","id":"GF61-8G1"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1365","date":"after 1365","place":"Oxton, Cheshi